## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: (e.g., Viscaria, Zhang Jike ALC). The best match for aggressive, close-to-table counter-attackers. The crispness complements the hard rubber perfectly.
    - Inner Carbon: (e.g., Hurricane Long 5). Excellent for players who want a bit more dwell time and a higher arc for looping from mid-distance.
    - All-Wood: Only recommended for hard 7-ply woods (e.g., Clipper). 5-ply woods will likely feel too slow and heavily head-weighted.
    - Mismatch Cases: Soft, slow 5-ply all-wood blades. The setup will feel horribly unbalanced, heavy, and lack the power to engage the sponge.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: The ideal placement. Perfectly suited for massive forehand power loops and dominant serve/receive.
    - Backhand: Only for elite players with exceptional backhand mechanics who prefer hard, low-throw rubbers. Too heavy and hard for most amateur backhands.

